íźźŕ≤Title: title: config env
Path: Examples
Content:
Open user's env.nu in the default editor.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> config env


```
Pretty-print a commented 
``env.nu``
 that explains common settings.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> config env --doc | nu-highlight,


```
Pretty-print the internal 
``env.nu``
 file which is loaded before the user's environment.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> config env --default | nu-highlight,


```
